title: Jarryd Hayne NFL: NRL stars flock to watch 49ers v Ravens
text:
Andrew Johns, Krisnan Inu, Feleti Mateo and Willie Tonga all travelled to watch Hayne.
The Daily Telegraph ANDREW Johns has joined a host of current and former NRL players at Levi’s Stadium on Monday to witness Jarryd Hayne turn out for the San Francisco 49ers.
Hayne didn’t enjoy one of his best performances in his sixth game of NFL, as the 49ers snared a crucial 25-20 win over Baltimore Ravens.
But that didn’t dampen the spirits of rugby league Immortal Johns who was pictured in the crowd in front of an Australian flag alongside a number of Hayne’s good mates, including Tony Williams, Krisnan Inu, Willie Tonga, Feleti Mateo, and Joseph and Junior Paulo.
AS IT HAPPENED: How did Hayne fare?
NFL WRAP: Broncos stay unbeaten
Hayne joined by former NRL mates NRL stars at 49ers The group were all sporting Hayne’s #38 49ers jersey, except for Johns, in a photo posted on Inu’s Instagram.
After being stood down from Channel Nine’s coverage of the NRL grand final two weeks ago due to an incident at Toowoomba airport, Johns has been holidaying in America.
Last week the former NRL great was spotted chatting to Andrew Bogut after a Golden State Warriors pre-season match at Oracle Arena, the home of the NBA champions.
Running back Jarryd Hayne #38 of the San Francisco 49ers Source: AFP
Hayne had one of his quietest games yet on a frustrating afternoon that started off on the wrong foot.
A tackle from behind from Baltimore’s Anthony Levine resulted in him spilling the ball for the third time in Hayne’s budding NFL career.
“I was obviously devastated with the fumble,” Hayne told reporters.
“We always talk about it; ‘the most dangerous man is the man you don’t see’
“I’m sure I’ll be asked about that during the week and for me, I kind of felt like behind was clear and I went for that little bit extra.”
Jarryd Hayne: 'Devastated with fumble' 0:33 NFL: The San Francisco 49ers came away with a 5-point win over Baltimore, but it wasn't all smiles for running back Jarryd Hayne.
